January,10th 1985. When we had the explosion in Saundersfoot no one did much about it. They have only pulled the roads up and put new gas pipes in.The roads look terrible and cars have to go through the harbour car park and when the holiday makers come there will be traffic jams.They won't come back for a holiday here.The windows are not in the shops yet.There are boards up-it looks horrible!No one is doing any thing about it.They just keep on having meetings.It looks so dull I will be glad when it is built back together again.
Kate Yarney Age 11 Saundersfoot C.P School
